    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 611.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The director of the French mint of Paris, who has
                    kindly furnished to Mr. Slaker, a gentleman recommended by the Department, all
                    the information he desired, asks the good offices of this embassy to obtain for
                    the collection of the mint one of the Lafayette memorial medals which was
                    recently struck in the United States. Occasions frequently arise for this
                    embassy to recommend American visitors to the officials of the Paris mint, and I
                    should be glad to comply, if possible, with the director’s request.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horace Porter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
